------SpringBoot Basic structure

my-project
│
├── src
│   └── main
│       ├── java
│       │    └── com.example.project
│       │          ├── controller
│       │          ├── service
│       │          ├── repository
│       │          ├── model
│       │          └── ProjectApplication.java
│
│       └── resources
│            ├── application.properties
│            ├── static
│            └── templates
│
└── pom.xml




---------------------------------------------------------------



Spring Boot ka actual flow:

Client
   ↓
Controller
   ↓
Service
   ↓
Repository
   ↓
Database




Response:

Database
   ↑
Repository
   ↑
Service
   ↑
Controller
   ↑
Client



-------------------------------------------------------


Ek Real Example

User API banate hai.

Controller
@GetMapping("/user")
public User getUser() {
    return userService.getUser();
}
Service
public User getUser() {
    return userRepository.findById(1L).get();
}
Repository
interface UserRepository extends JpaRepository<User,Long>
🔟 3 Golden Rules (Senior Developers Use This)
Rule 1

Controller me logic nahi likhte

❌ Wrong

@RestController
if(user.age>18)

✔ Correct

Controller → Service
Rule 2

Service me business logic

Rule 3

Repository me sirf database queries

🚀 Ek Secret Bataun (Spring Boot Fast Learning)

Spring Boot ko 3 cheezo me tod do:

1️⃣ Controller → API
2️⃣ Service → Logic
3️⃣ Repository → Database

Agar ye clear ho gaya to 80% Spring Boot samajh gaya.